message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with speech separation, which is a subfield of speech processing. cs.SI is also likely as the paper discusses the use of different front ends for speech separation. cs.LG is another possibility as the paper uses machine learning techniques such as deep clustering and permutation invariant training. cs.SD is more likely than cs.LG as the focus is on the signal processing aspect rather than the machine learning aspect. cs.SD and cs.SI are followed by cs.SD, cs.CL, and cs.SY as other possible sub-categories.
